* An OpenType feature file is a text file that contains the typographic layout feature specifications for an OpenType font in an easy-to-read format. It may also contain override values for certain fields in the font tables. It is read in during the creation or editing of an OpenType font.

- OpenType Feature File first developed in <a href="../lists/originCommunities.html#microsoft">Microsoft</a> and <a href="../lists/originCommunities.html#adobeSystems">Adobe Systems</a>
- file extensions for OpenType Feature File include fea
- GitHub supports <a href="https://github.com/Alhadis/language-fontforge" title="The package used for syntax highlighting by GitHub Linguist.">syntax highlighting</a> for OpenType Feature File
- Read more about OpenType Feature File on the web: 1.
 https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OpenType 1.

